---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<Base title="Tailwind Mini-Lab" description="Interactive Tailwind CSS playground examples" bodyClass="min-h-screen bg-slate-100 text-slate-900 flex flex-col" mainClass="max-w-3xl mx-auto p-6 space-y-8">
	<header class="space-y-2 text-center">
		<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold">Tailwind Mini-Lab</h1>
		<p class="text-slate-600">Each section shows a concept and a quick tweak to try. Change the class as suggested, save, and refresh.</p>
	</header>

	<!-- 1) Spacing scale -->
	<section class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm p-6 space-y-4">
		<div>
			<p class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-500 uppercase">1. Spacing</p>
			<p class="text-slate-700">Tailwind spacing uses numbers mapped to rems (e.g. 4 = 1rem, 8 = 2rem).</p>
		</div>
		<div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
			<div class="bg-emerald-100 text-emerald-900 p-4 rounded">Current: <code>p-4</code></div>
			<p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Try: change <code>p-4</code> to <code>p-10</code> or <code>p-2</code> to see padding scale.</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- 2) Color + hover states -->
	<section class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm p-6 space-y-4">
		<div>
			<p class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-500 uppercase">2. Colors & States</p>
			<p class="text-slate-700">Utilities are composable; hover: and focus: variants change state styles.</p>
		</div>
		<button class="px-4 py-2 rounded bg-blue-600 text-white font-semibold hover:bg-blue-700 focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-300 transition">
			Hover and focus me
		</button>
		<p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Try: swap <code>bg-blue-600</code> to <code>bg-rose-600</code>, or remove <code>hover:bg-blue-700</code> to see state change disappear.</p>
	</section>

	<!-- 3) Flexbox layout -->
	<section class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm p-6 space-y-4">
		<div>
			<p class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-500 uppercase">3. Flexbox</p>
			<p class="text-slate-700">Flex utilities arrange items; gap controls spacing.</p>
		</div>
		<div class="flex items-center justify-center gap-0 bg-slate-50 p-4 rounded">
			<span class="px-3 py-1 bg-slate-900 text-white rounded">Item A</span>
			<span class="px-3 py-1 bg-slate-200 text-slate-800 rounded">Item B</span>
			<span class="px-3 py-1 bg-slate-200 text-slate-800 rounded">Item C</span>
		</div>
		<p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Try: change <code>justify-between</code> to <code>justify-center</code>, or set <code>gap-4</code> to <code>gap-0</code>.</p>
	</section>

	<!-- 4) Typography and spacing -->
	<section class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm p-6 space-y-4">
		<div>
			<p class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-500 uppercase">4. Typography</p>
			<p class="text-slate-700">Font size and leading are independent utilities.</p>
		</div>
		<div class="space-y-2">
			<p class="text-lg leading-7 text-slate-800">This text uses <code>text-lg</code> with <code>leading-7</code>.</p>
			<p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Try: change to <code>text-2xl</code> and <code>leading-tight</code> to see tighter lines.</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- 5) Borders, radius, shadow -->
	<section class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm p-6 space-y-4">
		<div>
			<p class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-500 uppercase">5. Borders & Shadow</p>
			<p class="text-slate-700">You can stack border, radius, and shadow utilities.</p>
		</div>
		<div class="p-4 border border-slate-300 rounded-lg shadow">
			<p class="text-slate-800">Current: <code>border border-slate-300 rounded-lg shadow</code></p>
		</div>
		<p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Try: change <code>rounded-lg</code> to <code>rounded-full</code> for pill shape, or <code>shadow</code> to <code>shadow-2xl</code>.</p>
	</section>

	<!-- 6) Gradients and background -->
	<section class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm p-6 space-y-4">
		<div>
			<p class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-500 uppercase">6. Gradients</p>
			<p class="text-slate-700">Background gradients are utilities too.</p>
		</div>
		<div class="h-24 rounded bg-gradient-to-r from-indigo-500 via-sky-500 to-emerald-400"></div>
		<p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Try: swap <code>to-emerald-400</code> to <code>to-rose-400</code>, or change direction <code>bg-gradient-to-b</code>.</p>
	</section>

	<!-- 7) Responsive modifiers -->
	<section class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm p-6 space-y-4">
		<div>
			<p class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-500 uppercase">7. Responsive</p>
			<p class="text-slate-700">Prefix with breakpoints like <code>md:</code> to change at certain widths.</p>
		</div>
		<div class="bg-slate-50 p-4 rounded flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-center gap-3">
			<div class="px-3 py-1 bg-indigo-600 text-white rounded text-center">Stacks on mobile</div>
			<div class="px-3 py-1 bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-900 rounded text-center">Row on md+</div>
		</div>
		<p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Try: change <code>md:flex-row</code> to <code>md:flex-col</code>, or add <code>lg:gap-10</code> to see spacing grow on large screens.</p>
	</section>

	<!-- 8) Parent/child width with flex growth -->
	<section class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm p-6 space-y-4">
		<div>
			<p class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-500 uppercase">8. Parent/Child Width</p>
			<p class="text-slate-700">Inside a flex parent, children only grow if you let them. <code>flex-1</code> makes them share space; <code>flex-none</code> keeps intrinsic size.</p>
		</div>
		<div class="flex gap-3 bg-slate-50 p-4 rounded">
			<div class="px-3 py-2 bg-emerald-200 text-emerald-900 rounded flex-1 text-center">flex-1 (fills)</div>
			<div class="px-3 py-2 bg-amber-200 text-amber-900 rounded flex-1 text-center">flex-none (fits text)</div>
			<div class="px-3 py-2 bg-blue-200 text-blue-900 rounded flex-1 text-center">flex-[2] (2x space)</div>
		</div>
		<p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Try: change <code>flex-none</code> to <code>flex-1</code> to see it stretch, or remove <code>flex-[2]</code> to make all equal.</p>
	</section>

	<!-- 9) Grid vs flex inside a container -->
	<section class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm p-6 space-y-4">
		<div>
			<p class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-500 uppercase">9. Flex vs Grid</p>
			<p class="text-slate-700">Parent display changes how children flow. Flex is one-dimensional; grid is two-dimensional.</p>
		</div>
		<div class="bg-slate-50 p-4 rounded space-y-3">
			<div class="flex gap-2">
				<div class="px-3 py-2 bg-slate-200 text-slate-800 rounded flex-1 text-center">Flex item</div>
				<div class="px-3 py-2 bg-slate-200 text-slate-800 rounded flex-1 text-center">Flex item</div>
				<div class="px-3 py-2 bg-slate-200 text-slate-800 rounded flex-1 text-center">Flex item</div>
			</div>
			<p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Try: change the parent class above from <code>flex</code> to <code>grid grid-cols-3</code> (or <code>grid-cols-2</code>) to see the layout reflow.</p>
		</div>
	</section>
</Base>
